abstract: Antitrust is the nuclear bomb of regulatory moves, but at a moment when nearly everything in America seems contentious, proposals to break up internet giants are gaining support.
snippet: Antitrust is the nuclear bomb of regulatory moves, but at a moment when nearly everything in America seems contentious, proposals to break up internet giants are gaining support.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A decade ago, when the greed and carelessness of the financial industry came close to destroying the American economy, the overwhelming response by politicians and the public was: Meh. Almost instantly, all was forgiven and forgotten.

abstract: Legalization of marijuana has become a pillar of progressive politics, and a litmus test for candidates’ commitment to equal treatment for all races in policing and criminal justice.
snippet: Legalization of marijuana has become a pillar of progressive politics, and a litmus test for candidates’ commitment to equal treatment for all races in policing and criminal justice.
lead_paragraph: People in Colorado still remember John Hickenlooper’s crack after the state legalized marijuana, a move he opposed: “Don’t break out the Cheetos or Goldfish too quickly.”

abstract: Senator Elizabeth Warren has an interesting plan for reform. But it has shortcomings worth considering.
snippet: Senator Elizabeth Warren has an interesting plan for reform. But it has shortcomings worth considering.
lead_paragraph: AUSTIN, Tex. — Among the techies who attended the annual South by Southwest Interactive conference the past few days, the hottest topic of conversation — besides the swarms of drunken idiots careening around Austin on rented electric scooters — was Senator Elizabeth Warren’s ground-shaking proposal to break up large tech companies like Amazon, Google and Facebook.

abstract: The Democratic Party’s crowded field and messy rules could lead to months of infighting and an ugly convention.
snippet: The Democratic Party’s crowded field and messy rules could lead to months of infighting and an ugly convention.
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump’s low approval ratings have attracted a crush of Democrats vying to make him a one-term president. But he might have an unlikely ally in his re-election bid: Democrats’ mess of a primary system.

abstract: Thankfully, monopoly power is shaping up as a central issue in the 2020 campaign.
snippet: Thankfully, monopoly power is shaping up as a central issue in the 2020 campaign.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren’s announcement on Friday of a plan to break up major tech monopolies like Facebook and Google was critically important — not just as a policy proposal, but also as a sign of the return of antitrust to politics.

abstract: Big Tech is reducing consumer choice and harming innovation, according to a report ordered by the country’s top economic official.
snippet: Big Tech is reducing consumer choice and harming innovation, according to a report ordered by the country’s top economic official.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The expanding power of technology companies has become a talking point in the United States presidential race, a subject of debate in India and a top focus of regulators in the European Union. Now, Britain is adding its voice to the worldwide backlash.

abstract: Readers respond to three columns about increasing divisions within the party.
snippet: Readers respond to three columns about increasing divisions within the party.
lead_paragraph: What — or who — will it take to unite the Democratic Party? Last week, three columnists wrote about the growing rivalry between the party’s progressives and moderates, and speculated as to which contingent could produce a candidate strong enough to take the presidency in 2020.
